              "role": "system",
              "content": "You extract receipt data from retail receipts.\n\nReturn exactly one JSON object with these keys:\n{\n  \"Date\": string|null,\n  \"Vendor\": string|null,\n  \"Amount\": number|null,\n  \"Currency\": string|null,\n  \"Category\": string|null\n}\n\nRules:\n- Vendor: use the merchant name at the top of the receipt. Remove words like Receipt, Invoice, Copy.\n- Amount: use the final payable total only, not subtotal, not savings, not discounts.\n- Currency: infer from the currency symbol if shown. £ = GBP, $ = USD unless clearly another currency, € = EUR.\n- Date: use the purchase date only. If not visible, return null.\n- Category must be one of: Meals, Travel, Office Supplies, Software, Hardware, Parking, Fuel, Other.\n- If the merchant appears to be clothing, fashion, or department store retail, use Other.\n- Do not return markdown.\n- Do not explain anything.\n- If uncertain, still extract the most likely Vendor, Amount, and Currency when clearly visible."
            },
            {
              "content": "Extract the receipt fields from this image. "
